    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1987-02-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1987-02-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="217"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d217">
                <head>217. Memorandum From the President’s Assistant for National Security Affairs
                        (<persName corresp="#p_CFCIII_1">Carlucci</persName>) to President <persName
                        corresp="#p_RRW_1">Reagan</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d217fn1">Source: National Security Council,
                        National Security Council Institutional Files, Box SR–094, <gloss
                            target="#t_NSDD_1">NSDD</gloss> 261. Secret. Sent for action. Copies
                        were sent to <persName corresp="#p_BGHW_1">Bush</persName> and <persName
                            corresp="#p_RDT_1">Regan</persName>. <persName corresp="#p_PCL_1"
                            >Powell</persName> initialed the memorandum on behalf of <persName
                            corresp="#p_CFCIII_1">Carlucci</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian"
                            notAfter="1987-02-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                            notBefore="1987-02-17T00:00:00-05:00">undated</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Consultations on the <gloss target="#t_SDI_1">SDI</gloss> Program</item>
                </list>
                <p rend="sectiontitleital">Issue</p>
                <p>To provide direction for consultations with our allies and Congress on the <gloss
                        target="#t_SDI_1">SDI</gloss> program.</p>
                <p rend="sectiontitleital">Facts</p>
                <p>Following last Tuesday’s <gloss target="#t_NSPG_1">NSPG</gloss> discussion,<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d217fn2">See <ref target="#d211">Document 211</ref>.</note> we
                    prepared the draft <gloss target="#t_NSDD_1">NSDD</gloss> at <hi rend="italic"
                        >Tab A</hi>
                    <note n="3" xml:id="d217fn3">Printed as <ref target="#d218">Document
                        218</ref>.</note> to serve as a basis for consulting our allies and Congress
                    prior to your making any decisions on restructuring the <gloss target="#t_SDI_1"
                        >SDI</gloss> program. Both allied and Congressional leaders stress that they
                    expect such consultations to occur.</p>
                <p rend="sectiontitleital">Discussion</p>
                <p>The draft <gloss target="#t_NSDD_1">NSDD</gloss> sets for the approach to be used
                    in consultations in considerable detail. We believe such detail is essential to
                    ensure that a consistent message is communicated. The <gloss target="#t_NSDD_1"
                        >NSDD</gloss> also requests the Secretary of Defense to provide information
                    on <hi rend="italic">how</hi> the program might be restructured, and the State
                    Department Legal Advisor to complete his ongoing legal review.</p>
                <p>The draft <gloss target="#t_NSDD_1">NSDD</gloss> has been reviewed by your senior
                    advisors including the Secretaries of State and Defense. Their comments have
                    been included.</p>
                <p rend="sectiontitleital">Recommendation</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">OK NO</hi>
                </p>
                <p>____ ____ That you sign the draft <gloss target="#t_NSDD_1">NSDD</gloss> at <hi
                        rend="italic">Tab A</hi> setting forth guidance for consultations on <gloss
                        target="#t_SDI_1">SDI</gloss>.<note n="4" xml:id="d217fn4">An unknown hand
                        wrote a checkmark beneath the “OK” option.</note>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
